  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Apathy has been reported to occur after subthalamic nucleus stimulation (STN-DBS), a
      treatment of motor complications in advanced Parkinson's disease (PD). It is not known
      whether postoperative apathy is related to dopamine withdrawal or a side effect of STN DBS.
      The researchers investigated potential predictors of apathy, and the effect of dopamine
      agonist treatment.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
